result.execSummary:
The defendant Megan Rae Cook was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes:
Pay all applicable costs and surcharges and supervision fees while on probation on case 15CF1924 or civil judgment will be entered with tax intercept.

Court ordered all court costs, fees and surcharges be paid through collection by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of probation on 15CF1924. Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment and/or tax intercept or other means.

***Pursuant to 973.015, Court finds the defendant was under the age of 25 at the time of the offense, the charge is a class H or I felony or a misdemeanor, society would not be harmed and the defendant would benefit by expungement. Upon successful completion of the sentence, Court will grant expungement if defendant successfully completes sentence and has no further violations of the law, upon submission of motion.

IF FINES AND FEES ARE NOT PAID BY THE END OF PROBATION, COURT WILL STILL CONSIDER EXPUNGEMENT.
With credit for 25 days.  TIME SERVED DISPOSITION
